title: 'Rookie Blue' not returning after six seasons on Global
text:
'Rookie Blue' not returning after six seasons on Global 
THE CANADIAN PRESS Friday, October 16, 2015 03:25 PM EDT | Updated: 
TORONTO -- After six seasons of sudsy cop drama, the Canadian series "Rookie Blue" is no longer. 
Global says the show, which finished airing its sixth season in July, will not be returning. 
The network notes the show came to "a natural conclusion" with the season finale. 
Missy Peregrym, Gregory Smith, Ben Bass and Peter Mooney were among the stars of the beloved show about a group of young Toronto police officers. 
"Rookie Blue" netted strong ratings in Canada, and also aired on ABC in the U.S. 
It also got several Canadian Screen Award nominations. 
Shaw Media says it plans to continue working with the team behind "Rookie Blue," ICF Films and eOne, on a yet-to-be-announced new project. 
"After six seasons the series reached a natural conclusion and this season's finale was the perfect wrap up for both our rookies and for fans, especially with the marriage of our favourite couple, Sam and Andy," said Christine Shipton, senior vice president and chief creative officer of Shaw Media, in a statement.
